     3→ * PulseLearn Campus Hub – Course Service
     4→ * --------------------------------------
     5→ * This service contains all domain logic related to Courses—creation, retrieval,
     6→ * update, deletion, enrollment, and progress tracking.  A typical workflow:
     7→ *
     8→ * 1. Request hits the CourseController                 (MVC)
     9→ * 2. Controller delegates to CourseService             (Service Layer)
    10→ * 3. Service queries DB through Prisma ORM             (Repository Pattern)
    11→ * 4. Service publishes Course domain events to Kafka   (Event Backbone)
    12→ * 5. Service caches hot data in Redis                  (Performance)
    13→ *
    14→ * NOTE: Do not import this file directly from your controllers; always consume
    15→ * it via the service locator (`src/di/index.js`) to keep dependencies swappable
    16→ * and mock-able during tests.
    17→ */
